# .vscodeignore — controls what gets packaged into the .vsix
#
# NOTE: vsce 3.x ignores .gitignore when this file is present. All exclusions
# must be explicit here, including rules that would normally come from .gitignore.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Replicated from .gitignore (vsce does not apply .gitignore when .vscodeignore
# is present — everything must be listed explicitly)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

node_modules/
.git/
.vscode/
.vscode-test/
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.vsix
__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
vendor/
*.tensorbin
model_cache/
tensor_cache*/
site/
venv/
.backups/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Source / build files (compiled into dist/ by webpack + copy-content)
# The extension only needs the dist/ output at runtime.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

src/
test/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Build / CI / deployment tooling
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

scripts/
.github/
webpack.config.js
tsconfig.json
tsconfig.test.json
.mocharc.json
build.log
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.*
docker-compose.yml
podman-compose.yml
koyeb.yaml
.dockerignore
.env.example

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Developer / project tooling (machine-local, not useful to extension users)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

docs/
plans/
generated/
.claude/
.husky/
.aider*
CLAUDE.md
.gitignore
.gitmodules
.secretlintignore

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Source content / theme directories
#
# Both are copied into dist/ by the copy-content build step. Shipping the
# originals alongside dist/ doubles the file count for no benefit.
# The extension references dist/content/ and dist/themes/ at runtime.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

content/
themes/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GitHub Pages artifacts (not needed inside the VSCode extension)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

.nojekyll

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Session / scratch implementation notes
#
# Artefacts left in the repo root by aider / Claude Code sessions.
# Not user-facing documentation; not needed at extension runtime.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

QB2_*.md
QWEN3_*.md
IMPLEMENTATION_*.md
INSTALLATION_BUGS_FIXED.md
MODEL_ROULETTE_*.md
P300C_*.md
PYPI_*.md
TT_METAL_BUILD_*.md
TT_METAL_PRECOMPILED.md
VALIDATION_UPDATE_*.md
VERSION_UPDATE_*.md

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Backup / scratch files
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

**/*.backup

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Web-only dist assets (GitHub Pages — not the VSCode extension webview)
#
# lesson-web.js and lesson-web-vars.css are only used by the static site
# generated by `npm run build:web`.  The VSCode extension webview uses
# lesson-viewer.js and lesson-theme.css instead.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

dist/src/webview/scripts/lesson-web.js
dist/src/webview/styles/lesson-web-vars.css
